  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Support to the UN World Health Organisation (WHO) for the Syria crisis</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">To provide support to WHO to enable them to deliver health care to those affected by the conflict in Syria. This will be achieved by equipping primary and secondary health facilities with medical supplies and equipment, and through the provision of refresher training to health professionals.  The project will support the provision of disease detection systems and improved health information systems, offering real time data for decision-making to determine whether health is improving and where the needs are greatest. The project will also provide trauma care and mental health and psychosocial support services to those who have been affected by the conflict, including therapy and medication.</narrative>
  </description>
